Description: Innercircuit provides an innovative dependable option for property owners in collecting rent from tenants.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Innercircuit, Inc. provides an innovative, dependable option for property owners and managers to collect rent more quickly and efficiently from residents. Similar to receiving monthly eBills from utility companies or cell phone providers, Innercircuit sends property branded notifications to residents prompting online rent payment. Rent payment can be made anywhere an internet connection is available. With a click of a button, funds are directly deposited into a property's bank account. In conjunction with Innercircuit's rent collection software, we also provide a customized web-based community portal to allow tenants the opportunity to submit maintenance requests, access community news and announcements delivered via email, and meet other tenants. This allows tenants to have access to the community while at work, while at home on the weekends, or while the property management office is closed. From community to residents, it all begins with inspiration. Our team strives to create a customized residential portal for a community. Our product has been developed and enhanced based on personal living experiences in communities all across the United States. We are steadfastly creating web-based "virtual communities" by hastening the routines that we all become a part of in a community. We simplify property staff's job of responding to resident requests—oftentimes being the same questions asked over and over again. Our web-based philosophy offers a potential for efficiency, scalability, and integration with management software. The value of our product impacts resident retention, referrals, and satisfaction as well as a unique marketing tool to allure prospective tenants.
